# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules.
#
# Catch-all SPA fallback. Any path that doesn't match a static file or a
# Pages Function is served index.html with a 200 status, so the React
# router (app.jsx) can claim the route on the client. Without this, deep
# links like /articles/<slug> would 404 unless the Pages dashboard's
# "Single-page application" mode is enabled — pinning it here makes the
# behavior explicit and survives any dashboard change.
#
# The functions/_middleware.js runs first on every request and rewrites
# per-route <title>, meta, canonical, and JSON-LD for known routes
# (articles, sections, and the static page list) before this fallback
# applies. Unknown paths still get rendered by the React 'Not found'
# branch in app.jsx; consider tightening this if soft-404 reports show up.

/*    /index.html    200
